## Quiz

?? Why is it critical that chromosomes align at the metaphase plate *before* anaphase begins?
>> The cell has a "spindle assembly checkpoint" — anaphase only proceeds once every chromosome is attached to fibers from both poles. Skipping this check would mean sister chromatids might not separate evenly, producing daughter cells with the wrong number of chromosomes (aneuploidy).

?? How does mitosis differ from meiosis in its final outcome?
>> Mitosis produces two genetically identical diploid daughter cells (used for growth and repair). Meiosis produces four genetically distinct haploid daughter cells (used for sexual reproduction — sperm, eggs). Meiosis includes an extra round of division and a chromosome-shuffling step (crossing over).
